<br>
If you have a car, and one of your wheels go flat, you can still drive - slowly. Still most people would say that the car doesn't need mere tweaking, but a good repair.<br>
<br>
What Sony did was to take away an old, working wheel and replaced it with a new shiny one. That's ok. But Sony decided that because they could get with it from the garage the 15 meters to the street, it were ready for the speedway - and various people agree that it isn't. Now it looks like it doesn't work over 20mph. Does the wheel need tweaking? Or repair? Or get out the old working wheel? Or is all fine because you can drive great at 20mph?<br>
