<br>
This patch at least holds people accountable for their damage now.  The biggest difference is that now it has an adverse affect on the player, whereas the previous system was to the players advantage.  We've seen time and time again that anything patched which gives the player an advantage is fixed almost immediately.  Anything that's patched which isn't working correctly, but doesn't effect the player...is eventually fixed.  I'm not saying we should not be vocal by any means.  The only way it will get fixed is by being vocal, but there is a limit to it...post the concerns...post the evidence, continue posting evidence, and it will be fixed...sooner than later I would image.  Posting insults and over-dramatizing the things are just absurd. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=467159">Sergze Opowa</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> [65 <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.graffe.com/">Wizard</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->] (<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.thebod.org">Brothers of Darkness</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->)<br>
